<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.237971>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Systenus tenorio sp. nov. (holotype): a. male habitus, left lateral (terminalia removed); b. hypopygium, left lateral. S. flavifemoratus sp. nov. (holotype): c. male habitus, right lateral; d. hypopygium, left lateral. S. maculipennis sp. nov.: e. male habitus, left lateral (terminalia removed); f. hypopygium, left lateral. Abbreviations: cer, cercus; epan, epandrium; hyp, hypandrium; ph, phallus; st, sternite; sur, surstylus; tg, tergite; 6, 7, 8, abdominal segments." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/237971/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

